transcript.text: Hello, in this video we will learn about how to create custom sized product.
Let's talk about the key features and benefits.
It allows you to create large format printing products like custom banners, posters, yard signs, etcetera.
With a custom price calculation feature.
Customers can order a custom sized product by entering their own required width and height.
In the price calculator it allows you to select product specific measuring unit like MMM, inch etcetera.
In the designer studio, it allows your customers to design on a custom size canvas.
Let's have a look into admin.
Go to products, click on add button.
Here we need to add the product required details like name, product type, choose standard, select product category and choose price defining method as size based price that is dynamic size.
Enable product status by activating this button.
You can upload the product small image and add description details from here.
Now if we talk about the configuration part, choose the type of action button that you want to show on product front side.
There we have an option to choose a measuring unit whether inches, millimeter or a centimeter from this drop down list.
Now click on the save button.
Now in designer option, we need to put the margin details only and put the number of printing sides you want to give customers to design in the designer studio.
We name it as front here and click on save and continue button.
Now go to price section here we need to put area range over here and you need to put unit price corresponding to the range here.
You will get an option to import the data in bulk.
So you can enter the values using excel sheet and paste it over here and click on add button.
After that we have option to enter quantity based price.
First of all, you need to create an area range and then click on quantity based price.
Then here is a size range drop down where you need to select the particular size range and based on that you can put the quantity range.

Suppose you can put a range from one to 10 quantity and in front of that you need to put the unit price suppose 1.5 and then you can just save it and after that while final calculation on front system will take price lookup based on area and quantity range combination.
Next we have to additional options.
So you can enter the additional options over here.
Suppose you have additional option for example Brommets then we need to enter details as you can see here.
Mainly you will see option to select price calculation type based on multiple only with area or perimeter etcetera.
Here you need to enable price multiply by quantity button.
Enter all the additional option attributes and save it.
Then go to attribute price.
Here we need to put the attribute unit price in front of area range when we go to the front.
Here we can see custom size option to enter width and height which you want to put and also customer can convert unit as per their requirement.
Here are some more features which you can check in the settings custom size tab.

Here you can put some predefined sizes, restrict users to enter into particular width and height as well as you have an option to select area lookup whether you want only area based or area with quantity based.
Thanks for watching this video.
Feel free to connect with us in case of any queries queries.
